my party members who apparently had been having some trouble.  I hailed the GM, just because it seems the thing to do when you see one, sort of a recognition of someone important (at least in my world) and continued to camp out unaware of the the domino I had just flipped over.<br><br>Saturday morning, bright and early.  I was anxious to play since I hadn't gotten a chance on friday, and logged on only to be momentarily confused by my character selection screen.  After a few seconds and some mouse clicks I realzied my Beastlord had been renamed from Hobbess to Shobby.  I never got a warning, presumably because I had logged out too quickly for the GM to send me one.  I proceeded to petition and went about my day, trying not to be too annoyed.  11 HOURS of straight play time later I had recieve tell from a guide or GM.  I know its the weekend but to me that just means more people are going to be playing and more people will be having issues.  I checked several times during the day to see that my petition was still in the queue.  As my play time drew to a close I was feeling fairly frustrated, and went ahead and sent an email petition in via the EQ website.  So far the only email back I have recieved so far was an automated one telling me it had been recieved.<br><br>Jump ahead to yesterday (wednesday) the other day of the week when I get a large amount of continuous play time.  I decided to try a petition again.  This time I had some success.  About an hour later a guide sent me a message asking about my petition.  I politely explained to him the problem.  He looked at whatever guides look at and reported that their was no record of a name change.  As I tried not to laugh, he told me he would foward my petition to GM level.  Another hour later I recieved a tell from GM: Blixtev (or something close) who once more asked me about my problem.  As soon as he said &quot;how can I help YE&quot; I should have known it was hopeless to get my old name back.  Despite that I again politely explained about my name change, and for a round or two of tells I played somewhat dumb about the comic and insisted I was refering to Sir Thomas Hobbes the philosopher and not a major historical figure.  Getting frustrated I gave up and asked my friends for thoughts on a new name since I was entitled to a choice for one since my name hadn't been obscene, just borrowed from a comic.<br><br>After a brief disscussion we decided on Seboh, and the GM at first accepted it and dissapeared, and I thought life could go back to somewhat normal.  However not to be outdone the GM realized Seboh was just Hobbes backwards and with a letter missing and told me to stop with the calvin and hobbes theme (my last name is Nivlac).  He immidiately changed my name to Brungo of all things.  I was getting pretty annoyed at this point.  So to just end the issue I went with the other name my friends and I had come up with, Seboa.<br><br>Of course with every name change i went through my hot keys all dissapeared, which made playing more frustrating.<br><br>Don't the GM's have anything better to do than play name police?  <br>And overall I'm pretty p.o'd at the server wide gm system because it took the wonderful Luclin GM's away.  <br><br>I wanted to just scream at this GM.  &quot;HELP YE&quot;?!  It's a game, and I am a person in the real world with a problem, and the problem has put me outside the world, I need help from outside the game mechanics world.<br><br>The naming policy is way to arbitrary, or not lax enough.  Hobbes can be a persons name (I knew someone in high school with it) a last name, as can many other posibly policy violating names!<br><br>-Hobbess<br><br> <p>Did I post that?  Aww bugger!Zow-cow!</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/usilkysong.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Silkysong</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Beast Prince</span><br> 