ards its a violation?  What about Colnlin (Lincoln letters slightly shifted)?<br><br>I could be fine with not being able to have the name Hobbess.  However the game let me have it (which means it wasn't vetoed on creation), and numerous previous GM's had been fine with it.  I talked a bit with a gm on seperate wedding occasions, once had to email a gm asking for my character by name to be restored because he had been deleted by an accident at verants end, and never did they say to change my name, or that their was something wrong with it.  I don't think someone seeing my name pop up in a chat screen broke anyones sense of immersion in the game world.<br><br>But then 2 new GM's come along and have a hissy fit, I have to suffer.  I liked my name, as you can see here I use it all over the web and with email accounts.  The luclin GM's essentially gave me permission to be Hobbess, and then these two took it away.  It's like one parent saying you can have a cookie, and another saying no you can't.  Which one is right?<br><br>-Hobbess <p>Did I post that?  Aww bugger!Zow-cow!</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/uschezar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Schezar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Savage Hunter</span><br>  Posts: 518<br> <font color=#871F78>(8/15/02 2:22:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=190.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: From Hobbess to Shobby to Seboa and the serverwide GM sy</span><hr size=1> The one who enforces the policies is always right. <p>See me at: <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=47953">Schezarine's Sexay Stuff</a><BR>See my BST: <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=105950">Schezanna's Savage Suite</a><BR><BR>---I *am* the Chinpokomon master!</p